        <headline>Flash Flood Warning issued July 31 at 2:03PM EDT until July 31 at 6:00PM EDT by NWS Mount Holly NJ</headline>
        <description>FFWPHI

The National Weather Service in Mount Holly has issued a

* Flash Flood Warning for...
Northeastern Berks County in eastern Pennsylvania...
Lehigh County in eastern Pennsylvania...
Northwestern Bucks County in southeastern Pennsylvania...
Northeastern Montgomery County in southeastern Pennsylvania...

* Until 600 PM EDT.

* At 203 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated thunderstorms producing
heavy rain across the warned area. Between 1 and 2 inches of rain
have fallen. The expected rainfall rate is 1.5 to 3 inches in 1
hour. Additional rainfall amounts of 1 to 2 inches are possible in
the warned area. Flash flooding is ongoing or expected to begin
shortly.

HAZARD...Flash flooding caused by thunderstorms.

SOURCE...Radar.

IMPACT...Flooding of small creeks and streams, urban areas,
highways, streets, and underpasses as well as other
drainage and low lying areas.

* Some locations that may experience flash flooding include...
Allentown, Emmaus, Quakertown, Perkasie, Doylestown, Souderton,
Bedminster, Kutztown, Chalfont, Hatfield, East Greenville and
Dublin.
</description>
        <instruction>Turn around...don't drown when encountering flooded roads. Most
flood deaths occur in vehicles.</instruction>
